name: UTakeMetaData
doc:
Take meta-data that is stored on ULevelSequence assets that are recorded through the Take Recorder.
Meta-data is retrieved through ULevelSequence::FindMetaData<UTakeMetaData>()

methods.name: GenerateAssetPath
methods.doc: Generate the desired asset path for this take meta-data

methods.name: GetDescription
methods.doc: @return The user-provided description for this take

methods.name: GetDuration
methods.doc: @return The duration for this take

methods.name: GetFrameRate
methods.doc: @return The frame-rate for this take

methods.name: GetFrameRateFromTimecode
methods.doc: @return Get if we get frame rate from time code

methods.name: GetLevelOrigin
methods.doc: @return The Map used to create this recording

methods.name: GetLevelPath
methods.doc: @return The AssetPath of the Level used to create a Recorded Level Sequence

methods.name: GetPresetOrigin
methods.doc: @return The preset on which the take was originally based

methods.name: GetSlate
methods.doc: @return The slate for this take

methods.name: GetTakeNumber
methods.doc: @return The take number for this take

methods.name: GetTimecodeIn
methods.doc: @return The timecode in for this take

methods.name: GetTimecodeOut
methods.doc: @return The timecode out for this take

methods.name: GetTimestamp
methods.doc: @return The timestamp for this take

methods.name: IsLocked
methods.doc: Check whether this take is locked

methods.name: Lock
methods.doc: Lock this take, causing it to become read-only

methods.name: Recorded
methods.doc:
Check if this take was recorded (as opposed
to being setup for recording)

methods.name: SetDescription
methods.doc:
Set this take's user-provided description
@note: Only valid for takes that have not been locked

methods.name: SetDuration
methods.doc:
Set this take's duration
@note: Only valid for takes that have not been locked

methods.name: SetFrameRate
methods.doc:
Set this take's frame-rate
@note: Only valid for takes that have not been locked

methods.name: SetFrameRateFromTimecode
methods.doc: Set if we get frame rate from time code

methods.name: SetLevelOrigin
methods.doc: Set the map used to create this recording

methods.name: SetPresetOrigin
methods.doc:
Set the preset on which the take is based
@note: Only valid for takes that have not been locked

methods.name: SetSlate
SetTakeNumber
SetTimecodeIn

Set this take's timecode in
@note: Only valid for takes that have not been locked

methods.name: SetTimecodeOut
methods.doc:
Set this take's timecode out
@note: Only valid for takes that have not been locked

methods.name: SetTimestamp

methods.name: Unlock
methods.doc: Unlock this take if it is read-only, allowing it to be modified once again
